CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 23, 1954, pg. 15., reads: "Vice President Richard M. Nixon swung himself around with the crowd during his busy visit in Pittsburgh Tuesday... Bottom left: greetings for Republican Senators at Gateway Plaza with Walter (Deep Figure) Rainey in center... - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Members of Republican club of Allegheny County with signs supporting Vice President Richard Nixon, Senator James H. Duff, and Senator Edward Martin at Gateway Center, Downtown
